Apr 17, 2020



Since March 23, the Fed’s balance sheet has soared like no other time in history, shooting up to more than $6 trillion. This is thanks to the “extensive new measures” that Chairman Jerome Powell decided to deploy, as a monetary moon shot intended to avoid severe economic disruptions.





